1
00:00:00,033 --> 00:00:01,333
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,333 --> 00:00:02,833
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:07,300 --> 00:00:08,500
(Episode 9)

4
00:00:19,900 --> 00:00:25,433
<i>On the way to Mom's work</i>

5
00:00:25,433 --> 00:00:29,633
<i>White wild rose</i>

6
00:00:30,639 --> 00:00:35,728
<i>The white petals of the wild rose</i>

7
00:00:35,729 --> 00:00:39,233
<i>Taste good too</i>

8
00:00:39,907 --> 00:00:42,800
<i>On hungry days</i>

9
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:50,110
<i>I quietly picked and ate them</i>

10
00:00:51,791 --> 00:00:57,729
<i>Calling out "Mom, Mom"</i>

11
00:00:57,730 --> 00:01:02,733
<i>I ate them</i>

12
00:01:21,833 --> 00:01:24,000
Ma'am, what's wrong?

13
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:25,033
What do I do?

14
00:01:25,918 --> 00:01:27,300
Ma'am, what's wrong?

15
00:01:28,659 --> 00:01:29,759
Please wake up.

16
00:01:30,126 --> 00:01:31,926
Ma'am!

17
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:34,500
What should I do?

18
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:36,400
Please hold on, I'll call an ambulance.

19
00:01:39,153 --> 00:01:42,869
I'm fine, miss.

20
00:01:43,557 --> 00:01:44,818
Are you feeling better?

21
00:01:44,819 --> 00:01:46,619
Yes.

22
00:01:46,620 --> 00:01:51,704
I just got a little dizzy
from low blood pressure.

23
00:01:54,926 --> 00:01:56,326
Are you really okay?

24
00:01:56,790 --> 00:01:59,800
You look pale.
Do you want to go to a nearby hospital?

25
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:01,141
I'll take you.

26
00:02:01,142 --> 00:02:02,328
No.

27
00:02:02,329 --> 00:02:05,700
I'll just sit here and rest for a bit,

28
00:02:05,700 --> 00:02:07,400
so don't worry
and just go about your business.

29
00:02:08,254 --> 00:02:09,921
Still...

30
00:02:11,060 --> 00:02:13,093
I'm really fine.

31
00:02:14,893 --> 00:02:16,360
All right, then.

32
00:02:19,060 --> 00:02:20,860
Ma'am,

33
00:02:21,674 --> 00:02:23,160
do you happen to have a cell phone?

34
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:25,093
Why do you ask?

35
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:28,593
May I install something on it for you?

36
00:02:30,193 --> 00:02:30,960
Joy?

37
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:32,260
(How can I help you?)

38
00:02:32,260 --> 00:02:35,460
If you ever get lost or feel unwell,

39
00:02:35,460 --> 00:02:37,423
press this and tell it what you need.

40
00:02:37,424 --> 00:02:38,493
It can guide you,

41
00:02:38,493 --> 00:02:40,593
and find nearby police stations
or hospitals.

42
00:02:41,460 --> 00:02:44,060
And if you tap "Find Friends" here,

43
00:02:44,060 --> 00:02:46,560
you can chat with people your age...

44
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:48,060
and even find good restaurants.

45
00:02:48,060 --> 00:02:51,493
The world has gotten so convenient.

46
00:02:52,060 --> 00:02:54,601
Who made something fascinating like this?

47
00:02:55,160 --> 00:02:56,193
I did.

48
00:02:56,193 --> 00:02:58,093
I made this program.

49
00:02:58,093 --> 00:02:59,093
What?

50
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:02,993
You're amazing.

51
00:03:02,993 --> 00:03:05,860
I wanted to make it even easier
and more interesting,

52
00:03:05,860 --> 00:03:07,160
but I can't anymore.

53
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:10,060
- Why not?
- Something happened.

54
00:03:11,060 --> 00:03:12,860
Anyway, if you ever need anything,

55
00:03:12,860 --> 00:03:14,687
don't forget to open this.

56
00:03:15,460 --> 00:03:17,393
Thank you so much.

57
00:03:17,393 --> 00:03:18,760
It's nothing.

58
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:21,868
Please get home safely.

59
00:03:25,260 --> 00:03:26,460
Goodbye.

60
00:03:29,393 --> 00:03:32,060
What a lovely girl.

61
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:39,560
By the way,
I haven't seen Mother for a while.

62
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:40,860
Did she go somewhere?

63
00:03:41,193 --> 00:03:44,460
She went to the herbal shop
to get some medicine for Father.

64
00:03:44,460 --> 00:03:48,093
Why does she wear herself out
over something so pointless?

65
00:03:48,093 --> 00:03:50,593
It's not pointless.

66
00:03:51,260 --> 00:03:54,093
With you in this condition
and refusing treatment,

67
00:03:54,093 --> 00:03:56,160
she must be worried sick.

68
00:03:56,160 --> 00:03:57,693
He's right.

69
00:03:57,693 --> 00:04:00,193
Her devotion is remarkable.

70
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:02,160
What has gotten into you two?

71
00:04:04,693 --> 00:04:06,760
Madam,

72
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:09,360
you should've called me
if you were going to the herbal shop.

73
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:10,960
You're back, Mother.

74
00:04:12,860 --> 00:04:14,960
Did you carry all this by yourself?

75
00:04:15,593 --> 00:04:18,560
Next time, please take her with you.

76
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:20,560
She can learn about herbs
and carry things for you.

77
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:23,560
Right,
and we can even go on a little date.

78
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:28,293
Sounds like
someone's really buttering her up...

79
00:04:29,260 --> 00:04:31,360
when she's not even baking.

80
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:36,660
You should go inside.
I'll prepare some things before I come.

81
00:04:36,660 --> 00:04:38,060
Take your time.

82
00:04:38,060 --> 00:04:40,860
I'll go up to Gyeol's room for a bit.

83
00:04:45,260 --> 00:04:47,160
Going golfing? Shall I come too?

84
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:49,260
I'll be back.

85
00:04:49,260 --> 00:04:51,260
Why are you upset?

86
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:54,960
You should at least answer your mother.

87
00:05:00,260 --> 00:05:03,660
Why is he being like that?
Did something happen?

88
00:05:03,860 --> 00:05:06,193
No, nothing.

89
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:15,060
You still haven't apologized to Seung Ri?

90
00:05:15,060 --> 00:05:16,560
Whatever.

91
00:05:17,060 --> 00:05:18,793
He's my only son,

92
00:05:18,793 --> 00:05:20,460
yet he doesn't understand
his mother's heart at all.

93
00:05:20,660 --> 00:05:23,560
Watch what you say. Why "only son?"

94
00:05:32,660 --> 00:05:33,693
Grandpa.

95
00:05:34,260 --> 00:05:35,360
What were you doing?

96
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:37,660
I was looking over company materials.

97
00:05:37,660 --> 00:05:39,060
- Sit here.
- Okay.

98
00:05:41,107 --> 00:05:44,540
So, how is it? Manageable?

99
00:05:45,107 --> 00:05:46,507
Not yet.

100
00:05:46,507 --> 00:05:48,740
I have to learn step by step.

101
00:05:49,807 --> 00:05:52,407
For the initial setup and team formation,

102
00:05:53,307 --> 00:05:56,207
don't just follow your father or brother.

103
00:05:56,207 --> 00:05:57,607
Do it your way.

104
00:05:57,607 --> 00:05:59,740
Yes, Grandpa.

105
00:05:59,740 --> 00:06:02,607
By the way, I'm planning
to visit Mr. Seo's house later...

106
00:06:02,607 --> 00:06:03,940
and see Seung Ri's mother too.

107
00:06:03,940 --> 00:06:06,207
Good, you should.

108
00:06:07,107 --> 00:06:08,507
What's this?

109
00:06:09,707 --> 00:06:12,740
It's an AI program
from a startup that Min Ho acquired.

110
00:06:13,307 --> 00:06:15,840
I'm reviewing it
since it might be applicable...

111
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:17,407
to the retirement community project.

112
00:06:18,207 --> 00:06:20,707
Seeing how focused you are,

113
00:06:20,707 --> 00:06:23,840
Min Ho must've made a good move this time.

114
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:24,607
Of course.

115
00:06:30,007 --> 00:06:32,440
While I can still move,

116
00:06:34,940 --> 00:06:36,707
let's go see your father.

117
00:06:38,007 --> 00:06:40,340
Yes, I'll take you.

118
00:06:40,340 --> 00:06:41,340
All right.

119
00:06:54,307 --> 00:06:56,007
I hope I'm not too late.

120
00:06:56,940 --> 00:07:00,940
Please help Grandpa...

121
00:07:00,940 --> 00:07:02,207
stay here longer,

122
00:07:03,540 --> 00:07:04,507
Father.

123
00:07:08,740 --> 00:07:10,840
(Eldest son)

124
00:07:12,307 --> 00:07:13,640
The phone is off.

125
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:16,907
After the beep,
you'll be connected to voicemail.

126
00:07:16,907 --> 00:07:18,607
Additional charges may apply...

127
00:07:20,154 --> 00:07:21,440
Did something happen?

128
00:07:23,364 --> 00:07:25,040
I should go check.

129
00:07:27,507 --> 00:07:29,607
This may sound upsetting,

130
00:07:29,607 --> 00:07:33,107
but when you come,
please come when I'm home.

131
00:07:35,007 --> 00:07:36,740
It's not like I went for my own sake.

132
00:07:36,740 --> 00:07:38,540
I won't go again.

133
00:07:47,740 --> 00:07:50,007
Have I ever treated her...

134
00:07:50,007 --> 00:07:52,907
like other mothers-in-law do?

135
00:07:52,907 --> 00:07:57,310
I bring kimchi and side dishes,
fill their fridge,

136
00:07:57,507 --> 00:07:59,107
pick up and drop off their child,

137
00:07:59,107 --> 00:08:01,207
and help with housework.

138
00:08:03,407 --> 00:08:05,407
I didn't really...

139
00:08:05,407 --> 00:08:07,207
want to say this,

140
00:08:08,207 --> 00:08:10,440
but Eun Hyeong...

141
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:12,724
got hand eczema.

142
00:08:12,725 --> 00:08:14,107
- My goodness.
- What?

143
00:08:16,540 --> 00:08:19,907
How much housework did he do?

144
00:08:19,907 --> 00:08:22,440
She told me not to come
when she's not home.

145
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:24,540
Is that something
a daughter-in-law should say?

146
00:08:24,540 --> 00:08:28,807
I didn't think she was
that kind of person.

147
00:08:29,707 --> 00:08:33,340
Yesterday, I was so taken aback...

148
00:08:33,340 --> 00:08:35,307
I couldn't say anything and just left.

149
00:08:36,807 --> 00:08:38,540
I can actually understand her side.

150
00:08:39,107 --> 00:08:40,640
- What?
- Cho Rong,

151
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:43,607
are you taking her side
just because you're young too?

152
00:08:44,507 --> 00:08:46,140
It's not that.

153
00:08:46,140 --> 00:08:49,607
If someone keeps invading your privacy,
it's uncomfortable.

154
00:08:49,607 --> 00:08:51,307
Am I a stranger?

155
00:08:51,307 --> 00:08:54,050
I think of her like my own daughter!

156
00:08:57,107 --> 00:08:59,207
Enough.

157
00:08:59,207 --> 00:09:02,707
It's all ground. Why keep grinding?

158
00:09:03,140 --> 00:09:06,407
Our generation has it the hardest.

159
00:09:07,607 --> 00:09:08,840
We suffered under in-laws
when we were young,

160
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:11,007
and now under daughters-in-law.

161
00:09:11,007 --> 00:09:13,707
There's no generation stuck like ours.

162
00:09:14,307 --> 00:09:15,122
Yes, Mother.

163
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:18,718
Eun Hyeong didn't come home last night.

164
00:09:19,007 --> 00:09:20,007
What?

165
00:09:21,053 --> 00:09:23,109
He stayed out overnight?

166
00:09:27,040 --> 00:09:29,707
After saying he'd be late drinking
with the department head,

167
00:09:29,707 --> 00:09:31,230
his phone's been off.

168
00:09:31,540 --> 00:09:35,240
Did he say anything about being appointed?

169
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:37,707
No.

170
00:09:37,707 --> 00:09:40,040
Mother, I have to go to a wedding.

171
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:41,200
I'll hang up now.

172
00:09:41,540 --> 00:09:44,107
What? Okay.

173
00:09:46,607 --> 00:09:48,907
What's going on?

174
00:09:49,907 --> 00:09:52,907
Eun Hyeong is not the type to stay out.

175
00:10:01,834 --> 00:10:04,807
Why wouldn't the door let me in?

176
00:10:04,807 --> 00:10:06,440
I changed the passcode.

177
00:10:08,195 --> 00:10:09,514
You reek of alcohol!

178
00:10:09,515 --> 00:10:11,043
Why change it suddenly?

179
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:14,013
Did you try to lock me out
because I stayed out?

180
00:10:14,746 --> 00:10:15,746
What?

181
00:10:18,707 --> 00:10:20,807
I'm really sorry.

182
00:10:20,807 --> 00:10:22,807
I crossed the river
of forgetfulness called alcohol...

183
00:10:22,807 --> 00:10:25,040
and didn't even realize my phone had died.

184
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:26,840
Forget that.

185
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:29,107
I want to know why you got so drunk.

186
00:10:30,307 --> 00:10:32,207
But I'm on my way to a wedding.

187
00:10:32,707 --> 00:10:33,607
A wedding?

188
00:10:33,607 --> 00:10:35,827
We were supposed to go together.

189
00:10:35,828 --> 00:10:37,107
Right, I'll get ready...

190
00:10:39,407 --> 00:10:40,707
Forget it!

191
00:10:41,507 --> 00:10:42,907
Charge your phone.

192
00:10:42,907 --> 00:10:44,140
Mother's been waiting for your call.

193
00:10:44,807 --> 00:10:46,407
Seriously!

194
00:10:46,407 --> 00:10:47,407
Bye.

195
00:10:53,507 --> 00:10:57,707
It's your day off.
Why come out instead of taking a nap?

196
00:10:57,707 --> 00:11:01,040
I'm not used to it, so I can't sleep.

197
00:11:01,807 --> 00:11:02,940
Did you go somewhere?

198
00:11:03,707 --> 00:11:05,007
I went to Cho Rong's place.

199
00:11:06,007 --> 00:11:07,140
By the way,

200
00:11:07,140 --> 00:11:10,507
I think something happened to Eun Hyeong.

201
00:11:10,507 --> 00:11:12,940
He said he was meeting
the department head yesterday,

202
00:11:12,940 --> 00:11:15,040
but his phone's still off.

203
00:11:16,540 --> 00:11:19,340
Ji Seon said he stayed out overnight.

204
00:11:19,340 --> 00:11:21,107
What? He stayed out?

205
00:11:21,507 --> 00:11:23,107
Mom,

206
00:11:23,107 --> 00:11:26,007
he's almost 40, not a teenager.

207
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:29,407
That can happen when drinking.

208
00:11:29,407 --> 00:11:31,307
No, it can't.

209
00:11:31,307 --> 00:11:34,249
It's never happened before.

210
00:11:34,407 --> 00:11:39,707
Stop thinking you know everything
about him.

211
00:11:39,707 --> 00:11:41,040
Dr. Cho,

212
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:44,154
are you rebelling against my parenting?

213
00:11:44,407 --> 00:11:46,440
Not rebelling,

214
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:48,340
just stating my opinion.

215
00:11:48,340 --> 00:11:50,082
She has a point.

216
00:11:50,083 --> 00:11:52,340
There's a saying,
"Children eventually leave your arms."

217
00:11:52,340 --> 00:11:54,207
He'll call soon.

218
00:11:54,207 --> 00:11:55,340
I'm going to the library.

219
00:11:55,340 --> 00:11:56,440
Wait, Eun Nim.

220
00:11:59,107 --> 00:12:01,807
Make sure you eat properly while studying.

221
00:12:01,807 --> 00:12:03,007
You need...

222
00:12:03,007 --> 00:12:05,507
stamina to study. Got it?

223
00:12:05,507 --> 00:12:07,340
Thank you. I'm off.

224
00:12:07,340 --> 00:12:08,407
Okay.

225
00:12:15,307 --> 00:12:17,142
- I'm back.
- Hey.

226
00:12:17,707 --> 00:12:19,340
Why do you look so down?

227
00:12:19,340 --> 00:12:21,440
It's nothing.

228
00:12:24,307 --> 00:12:26,107
What's wrong with her?

229
00:12:26,107 --> 00:12:29,507
She got the investment confirmation
from Kangsu Construction.

230
00:12:30,107 --> 00:12:32,007
She should be celebrating.

231
00:12:32,007 --> 00:12:33,640
Kangsu Construction's legal team?

232
00:12:35,807 --> 00:12:37,407
I'll go check on Eun Ae.

233
00:12:41,107 --> 00:12:43,540
This is tricky. Should I go or not?

234
00:12:45,907 --> 00:12:48,760
If you keep protesting
and causing trouble,

235
00:12:48,761 --> 00:12:50,607
they'll file a lawsuit.

236
00:12:50,607 --> 00:12:54,165
I don't think this is just a warning.

237
00:12:54,166 --> 00:12:56,640
What should I do, Dad?
Is there any way out of this?

238
00:12:57,240 --> 00:13:00,007
I went to a free legal consultation,

239
00:13:00,007 --> 00:13:01,707
but they said they need
to see the contract.

240
00:13:01,707 --> 00:13:03,896
They can't help
unless they know the details.

241
00:13:04,740 --> 00:13:05,807
Of course.

242
00:13:06,305 --> 00:13:09,495
But how am I supposed to get it?

243
00:13:11,507 --> 00:13:12,540
Dad,

244
00:13:12,540 --> 00:13:15,007
can you help me?

245
00:13:15,007 --> 00:13:17,540
Me? How?

246
00:13:17,540 --> 00:13:20,207
You can enter that room, right?

247
00:13:20,207 --> 00:13:23,240
Pretend to clean
and secretly copy the contract.

248
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:24,740
No!

249
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:25,740
That's illegal.

250
00:13:25,740 --> 00:13:27,907
I know, but...

251
00:13:27,907 --> 00:13:30,507
People say it's always better
to take the long way around.

252
00:13:30,507 --> 00:13:33,607
You need to solve this step by step.

253
00:13:34,607 --> 00:13:36,307
And...

254
00:13:36,307 --> 00:13:39,425
I'm thinking of quitting
the job at Kangsu Construction soon.

255
00:13:40,107 --> 00:13:41,507
Quit what?

256
00:13:41,507 --> 00:13:42,388
What?

257
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:45,940
What do you mean quit?

258
00:13:47,307 --> 00:13:49,040
Didn't you just say
that you were quitting?

259
00:13:49,540 --> 00:13:52,640
Mom, you're silly.

260
00:13:52,640 --> 00:13:55,407
The dumplings
at that place Dad and I went to...

261
00:13:55,407 --> 00:13:57,340
the other day were really good.

262
00:13:58,507 --> 00:13:59,707
Dumplings?

263
00:14:00,739 --> 00:14:01,940
You two are acting suspicious.

264
00:14:01,940 --> 00:14:03,707
Well, dumplings aside,

265
00:14:03,707 --> 00:14:06,207
we were talking about your trip.

266
00:14:06,593 --> 00:14:09,307
Yeah, that's right. Our trip to Europe.

267
00:14:09,840 --> 00:14:13,807
Eun Ae said Western Europe
is much better...

268
00:14:13,807 --> 00:14:15,940
as a self-planned trip
than a package tour.

269
00:14:15,940 --> 00:14:19,707
Right, package tours are tiring.

270
00:14:21,307 --> 00:14:22,507
Really?

271
00:14:23,102 --> 00:14:26,772
Anyway,
when do you think you can take time off?

272
00:14:26,940 --> 00:14:27,907
What?

273
00:14:27,907 --> 00:14:31,107
I haven't set the dates yet,
but I will soon.

274
00:14:32,260 --> 00:14:33,260
But why did you come up here?

275
00:14:34,140 --> 00:14:36,707
The more I think about it,
the less I like it.

276
00:14:36,707 --> 00:14:39,240
Come with me to Eun Hyeong's place.

277
00:14:40,907 --> 00:14:43,398
Something must have gone wrong.
I have a bad feeling.

278
00:14:43,607 --> 00:14:45,164
Why? Did something happen to him?

279
00:14:45,307 --> 00:14:47,179
No, he's just not answering his phone.

280
00:14:48,507 --> 00:14:51,507
Well, we can go see Bit Na too.

281
00:14:53,807 --> 00:14:54,807
Get some rest.

282
00:14:55,607 --> 00:14:57,407
- Okay, see you later.
- All right.

283
00:15:17,307 --> 00:15:19,207
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

284
00:15:20,107 --> 00:15:22,907
I was just about to sit here.

285
00:15:23,607 --> 00:15:26,607
Too bad. My bag sat here first.

286
00:15:28,107 --> 00:15:31,507
I'm saying I claimed this seat first.

287
00:15:31,507 --> 00:15:33,707
And I definitely saw you
behind me earlier.

288
00:15:33,707 --> 00:15:35,507
This isn't right.

289
00:15:39,740 --> 00:15:41,307
Okay.

290
00:15:41,766 --> 00:15:42,899
Excuse me?

291
00:15:43,140 --> 00:15:47,428
I feel a bit awkward saying this myself...

292
00:15:49,107 --> 00:15:53,940
But actually, I'm an artist.

293
00:15:56,307 --> 00:15:59,150
- An artist?
- Yes, an artist.

294
00:15:59,151 --> 00:16:01,207
For a creative artist, a seat...

295
00:16:01,207 --> 00:16:02,840
isn't just a seat.

296
00:16:02,840 --> 00:16:04,740
It means something more.

297
00:16:05,107 --> 00:16:07,207
The sunlight that day, the wind,

298
00:16:07,207 --> 00:16:09,940
the direction of the air,
the angle of the light...

299
00:16:11,407 --> 00:16:14,440
All of that affects my work.

300
00:16:15,707 --> 00:16:18,407
- Is that so?
- Yes.

301
00:16:19,340 --> 00:16:21,407
I'm glad you understand.

302
00:16:21,407 --> 00:16:23,007
Thank you.

303
00:16:28,640 --> 00:16:30,007
- Would you like to order?
- Yes.

304
00:16:30,007 --> 00:16:31,907
- One iced Americano, please.
- Darn it.

305
00:17:04,007 --> 00:17:05,140
Are you satisfied now?

306
00:17:05,907 --> 00:17:07,607
Yes, you'll be blessed.

307
00:17:14,707 --> 00:17:16,540
What a wacko.

308
00:17:31,607 --> 00:17:34,240
This isn't it.

309
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:49,340
What the? Is he a pervert or what?

310
00:17:51,007 --> 00:17:52,907
I wish I hadn't seen that.

311
00:17:55,807 --> 00:17:58,440
Yes, this is it.

312
00:17:58,440 --> 00:18:01,007
The delicate trembling of these muscles,

313
00:18:01,807 --> 00:18:04,607
the movement of the flesh.

314
00:18:05,407 --> 00:18:06,607
Okay.

315
00:18:08,707 --> 00:18:11,107
When did this cafe get so trashy?

316
00:18:21,807 --> 00:18:23,807
No, it's fine.

317
00:18:23,807 --> 00:18:25,840
My laptop didn't get wet, so don't worry.

318
00:18:32,207 --> 00:18:33,807
What are you doing? Let go of my hand.

319
00:18:39,307 --> 00:18:41,207
You pervert!

320
00:18:55,907 --> 00:18:58,007
I'm going to destroy you.

321
00:18:58,607 --> 00:19:01,607
I should've visited you sooner.
I'm sorry I'm late.

322
00:19:02,607 --> 00:19:05,007
You just got here
and had to deal with your grandfather...

323
00:19:05,007 --> 00:19:07,507
and the company,
so of course you've been busy.

324
00:19:07,507 --> 00:19:08,774
Do you have a girlfriend?

325
00:19:10,707 --> 00:19:13,852
Honey, that's a rude question.

326
00:19:14,407 --> 00:19:16,840
It's all right. I don't have one yet.

327
00:19:20,440 --> 00:19:21,607
Is that you, Seung Wu?

328
00:19:23,807 --> 00:19:25,740
- Thank you for the food.
- Eat up.

329
00:19:27,107 --> 00:19:28,707
What brings you here, Chief Ko?

330
00:19:28,707 --> 00:19:31,107
I wanted to see you, Mother.

331
00:19:32,007 --> 00:19:34,205
- Welcome, Chief Ko.
- Yes, sir.

332
00:19:34,206 --> 00:19:36,007
Gyeol, you were here too?

333
00:19:36,007 --> 00:19:37,007
Yes.

334
00:19:37,540 --> 00:19:39,007
I should get going now.

335
00:19:40,607 --> 00:19:41,940
Already?

336
00:19:41,940 --> 00:19:44,507
Stay and have dinner.
See Seung Wu too when he gets back.

337
00:19:44,507 --> 00:19:46,140
I'll visit again.

338
00:19:46,140 --> 00:19:48,240
- See you at work, sir.
- All right.

339
00:19:48,240 --> 00:19:49,407
I'll get going, Seung Ri.

340
00:19:52,454 --> 00:19:55,240
If you leave as soon as I arrive,
I'll feel bad.

341
00:19:55,240 --> 00:19:57,440
No, I was just about to get up.

342
00:19:57,440 --> 00:19:58,163
See you at home.

343
00:19:59,007 --> 00:20:00,707
- I'll be going.
- All right.

344
00:20:03,907 --> 00:20:05,207
What are you doing? Come sit down.

345
00:20:05,607 --> 00:20:06,707
Yes.

346
00:20:14,907 --> 00:20:17,207
First of all, I'm sorry, Mother.

347
00:20:17,207 --> 00:20:18,307
My mother made a mistake.

348
00:20:18,307 --> 00:20:21,807
Yes, a very big mistake.

349
00:20:21,807 --> 00:20:22,940
How could she do that to our Seung Ri?

350
00:20:22,940 --> 00:20:24,607
I sincerely apologize again.

351
00:20:24,607 --> 00:20:26,640
My mother will apologize soon as well.

352
00:20:27,507 --> 00:20:29,707
You two talk. I have somewhere to be.

353
00:20:38,931 --> 00:20:39,840
I'll be going now.

354
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:41,707
Where are you going?

355
00:20:41,707 --> 00:20:42,707
You're going to the office again,
aren't you?

356
00:20:43,307 --> 00:20:45,811
That's a serious work addiction!

357
00:20:47,807 --> 00:20:50,307
Chief Ko, let's talk for a moment.

358
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:53,840
Yes.

359
00:21:09,907 --> 00:21:12,007
You were home?

360
00:21:12,007 --> 00:21:13,307
Why didn't you answer your phone?

361
00:21:13,307 --> 00:21:14,907
Do you know how worried I was?

362
00:21:15,640 --> 00:21:17,107
I drank too much yesterday.

363
00:21:18,207 --> 00:21:20,407
By the way, what's with the front door?

364
00:21:23,007 --> 00:21:25,807
Did Ji Seon change the passcode...

365
00:21:25,807 --> 00:21:27,207
so I couldn't get in?

366
00:21:28,107 --> 00:21:29,928
Why are you saying nonsense like that?

367
00:21:30,107 --> 00:21:31,407
So it is true.

368
00:21:31,407 --> 00:21:34,605
She told me not to come when she's gone,
and now she changed the passcode.

369
00:21:34,606 --> 00:21:36,407
What are you talking about?

370
00:21:36,407 --> 00:21:38,376
Ji Seon told you not to come here?

371
00:21:38,507 --> 00:21:41,840
It's not like that.
Your mother just misunderstood.

372
00:21:43,207 --> 00:21:46,807
So what happened
with the department head yesterday?

373
00:21:48,607 --> 00:21:49,607
Don't tell me...

374
00:21:50,207 --> 00:21:51,607
Nothing's been decided yet.

375
00:21:51,607 --> 00:21:52,907
I just have to wait a little longer.

376
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:55,307
You gave me quite a scare.

377
00:21:56,707 --> 00:22:00,077
You can't even drink much,
so why did you drink so much?

378
00:22:00,078 --> 00:22:03,007
Well, we were talking about the future
of the philosophy department,

379
00:22:03,007 --> 00:22:04,807
the essence of scholarship,
and things like that...

380
00:22:13,007 --> 00:22:15,907
- There's our Bit Na.
- Grandma, Grandpa.

381
00:22:15,907 --> 00:22:17,507
Hi.

382
00:22:17,507 --> 00:22:20,519
You just woke up from your nap?

383
00:22:23,442 --> 00:22:25,107
Is Dad sick?

384
00:22:25,107 --> 00:22:27,240
What? No, he's not sick.

385
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:28,807
I think he just has an upset stomach.

386
00:22:31,286 --> 00:22:33,419
I wonder if he even had
a proper hangover meal.

387
00:22:34,340 --> 00:22:35,440
Bean sprouts...

388
00:22:37,728 --> 00:22:39,640
Is she going to get upset again
that I came over...

389
00:22:39,640 --> 00:22:41,061
and touched things while she wasn't here?

390
00:22:41,062 --> 00:22:44,540
That's one thing,
but first, he needs to eat something.

391
00:22:44,540 --> 00:22:46,207
His stomach is completely upside down.

392
00:22:47,180 --> 00:22:50,889
If she took proper care of him,
why would I have to do this?

393
00:22:52,407 --> 00:22:55,005
Bit Na, shall we play with blocks?

394
00:22:55,006 --> 00:22:56,228
Yes, Grandpa.

395
00:22:56,807 --> 00:22:58,307
Come on, let's go inside.

396
00:22:59,107 --> 00:23:01,739
I know how you feel about Seung Ri.

397
00:23:01,740 --> 00:23:04,181
But not everything...

398
00:23:04,182 --> 00:23:06,540
goes the way you want.

399
00:23:06,540 --> 00:23:09,907
Yes, I know. But I won't give up.

400
00:23:09,907 --> 00:23:12,904
I'll keep trying
until Seung Ri opens her heart.

401
00:23:13,107 --> 00:23:15,240
Honestly, this isn't only
a matter between the two of you.

402
00:23:17,507 --> 00:23:20,098
I don't have any ill feelings
toward you, Min Ho.

403
00:23:22,807 --> 00:23:25,207
But just look at what happened this time.
How could she...

404
00:23:25,207 --> 00:23:27,907
You know what my mother is like.
She's simple.

405
00:23:27,907 --> 00:23:30,507
No matter what, I'll try harder, Mother.

406
00:23:30,840 --> 00:23:34,540
Do you really think this can be solved
by just trying harder?

407
00:23:35,640 --> 00:23:38,607
- What?
- If you truly love someone,

408
00:23:38,607 --> 00:23:40,107
shouldn't respecting...

409
00:23:40,840 --> 00:23:43,207
how they feel come first,
rather than blindly trying harder?

410
00:23:47,207 --> 00:23:49,307
You're having dinner at Eun Hyeong's?

411
00:23:49,307 --> 00:23:52,707
Okay, I'll get my own dinner.

412
00:24:19,440 --> 00:24:21,307
I'm sorry, Dad.

413
00:24:21,307 --> 00:24:24,607
I'm just borrowing it for a moment.
I'll put it right back.

414
00:24:28,186 --> 00:24:30,486
(Kangsu Construction)

415
00:24:41,593 --> 00:24:43,026
Gyeol!

416
00:24:44,507 --> 00:24:46,107
Why did you come out?

417
00:24:46,107 --> 00:24:47,518
To go on a date with you.

418
00:24:48,307 --> 00:24:49,807
Seung Ri.

419
00:24:49,807 --> 00:24:52,307
I'm joking. Why are you so serious?

420
00:24:52,307 --> 00:24:54,907
I'm going to the office
to back up some files.

421
00:24:54,907 --> 00:24:58,123
Mr. Seo was worried you're a workaholic.
I guess he was right.

422
00:24:59,040 --> 00:25:01,207
Dad said that? When?

423
00:25:01,207 --> 00:25:03,307
When you got promoted to manager.

424
00:25:03,307 --> 00:25:05,265
He was so proud,

425
00:25:05,266 --> 00:25:07,107
saying you earned
that rapid promotion all on your own.

426
00:25:07,707 --> 00:25:10,107
He was worried
you might be a workaholic too.

427
00:25:10,507 --> 00:25:12,440
My dad secretly has
a soft spot for his daughter.

428
00:25:13,107 --> 00:25:15,540
He hardly says more than a few words
at home,

429
00:25:15,540 --> 00:25:17,807
but he loves the family fiercely.

430
00:25:17,807 --> 00:25:19,132
Although other people may not know.

431
00:25:19,133 --> 00:25:20,640
I know too.

432
00:25:20,640 --> 00:25:23,307
He's always been so warm to me.

433
00:25:25,407 --> 00:25:27,007
Using formal speech at work...

434
00:25:27,007 --> 00:25:29,340
and then speaking casually outside feels
a little awkward, doesn't it?

435
00:25:29,340 --> 00:25:31,607
Isn't that obvious? We're professionals.

436
00:25:31,940 --> 00:25:33,107
Professionals?

437
00:25:33,107 --> 00:25:35,107
I'm not.

438
00:25:35,107 --> 00:25:37,140
I spent my whole life
immersed in architecture,

439
00:25:37,140 --> 00:25:39,507
and now that I suddenly have to work
at a company, everything is hard.

440
00:25:41,440 --> 00:25:42,840
Manager Seo Seung Ri,

441
00:25:42,840 --> 00:25:45,040
I look forward to your guidance
from now on.

442
00:25:48,219 --> 00:25:49,819
Of course, Manager.

443
00:25:52,807 --> 00:25:55,407
He hasn't changed at all,
always drawing the line.

444
00:26:49,240 --> 00:26:50,307
Gyeol.

445
00:26:51,007 --> 00:26:52,307
Seung Ri.

446
00:27:00,040 --> 00:27:01,107
No!

447
00:27:07,040 --> 00:27:08,840
Get a grip, Ko Min Ho.

448
00:27:23,307 --> 00:27:24,540
(Lucky Joy Tech Intellectual Property
and Acquisition Agreement)

449
00:27:24,540 --> 00:27:25,607
Found it.

450
00:27:40,040 --> 00:27:41,040
Who's that?

451
00:27:42,140 --> 00:27:43,307
Who are you?

452
00:27:53,073 --> 00:27:56,040
(Our Happy Days)

453
00:27:56,041 --> 00:27:57,807
There will be absolutely no settlement
or leniency.

454
00:27:57,807 --> 00:27:59,607
Chief!

455
00:27:59,607 --> 00:28:01,707
I'm really sorry about that day.

456
00:28:01,707 --> 00:28:03,540
You know I've always had a fiery temper.

457
00:28:03,540 --> 00:28:05,840
I'll take it as if no apology was made.

458
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:08,686
I can't guarantee
what else that woman might do.

459
00:28:08,687 --> 00:28:11,707
That's exactly why I think it'd be better
to handle this quietly.

460
00:28:11,707 --> 00:28:13,240
- Go inside.
- No.

461
00:28:13,240 --> 00:28:16,440
No!

462
00:28:17,599 --> 00:28:19,599
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
